      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "Need to think this through - and review the WIP I had started. I believe when a service is \"retrieved\" via java.util service API there is one instance of that class returned. So, if we were to support multiple instances of a control loop event happening, then you wouldn't want to local variables like this. But rather have saved in memory one object per event. This allows for multi-threading etc. \n\nSee this review: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/policy/models/+/91882\n\nstartOperation is the method to kick things off. An object such as ControlLoopOperation would contain variables specific to the event (eg Policy, AAI details, response, requestId, subRequestId).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 57,
        "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pd1248@att.com",
        "username": "pdragosh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 11:34:48.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
