      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 63,
      "message": "Sure makes sense, i will remove the local variables. \nRegarding other variables specific to the event, I need VirtualControlLoopEvent (requestId), ControlLoopOperation (subReqId), Policy (payload, actors) objects. I wanted to separate the AAI params as key-value pairs to give flexibility to the rule-engine to do any sort of AAI enrichment/filtering versus bringing in the specific AAI param (e.g.  targetEntity like we have today). This is because CDS actor would need more than one AAI param. What do you think?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 159,
        "name": "Rashmi Pujar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rashmi.c.pujar@gmail.com",
        "username": "rashmi.pujar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-09-03 20:08:49.000000000",
